[COLOR=#e64a19][SIZE=5][B]Developer Corner[/B][/SIZE][/COLOR]
[SIZE=4][I]By Navarr[/I][/SIZE]

Hi all, Navarr here! I did a less than stellar job of being on top of the developers this month for updates. As such, we don’t have a lot of juicy goodness for you to read. That said, here’s the reports I got:

[COLOR=#e64a19][SIZE=4][B]Robertthegoat[/B][/SIZE][/COLOR]
Robert spent his time this month working on Gold Rush and participating in the development stream. He also worked on a couple secret items that we hope to reveal to you in gameplay within the next couple quarters.

[COLOR=#e64a19][SIZE=4][B]DocCodeSharp[/B][/SIZE][/COLOR]
Doc spent a lot of this month working on infrastructure projects such as tackling issues with servers coming online and modernizing our deployment stack. In addition, he continued his work on refactoring the MineZ codebase for performance, stability, and general bugfixing purposes.

[COLOR=#e64a19][SIZE=4][B]Skillerfox3[/B][/SIZE][/COLOR]
Skiller continued his work on Gold Rush this month, including some initial work on balancing general gameplay. You’ve heard Murg refer to a large issue of “snowballing” where when one team is in the lead it becomes far too difficult to take it from them - this is one of those core balancing issues we’ll be focusing on both before and during the alpha testing phases. Skiller also worked on some admin tooling - improving our staff’s lives so we can improve your experience in the games.

And that’s all I have! I hope to tell you more next month, but until then - this is Navarr signing off!

With that, I bid you farewell. I'm your host, Mistri. Please let us know what you think about the New Moon in the comments. We love to hear your feedback!